Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: The Problem Manager is responsible for managing the lifecycle of all Problems. His primary objectives are to prevent Incidents from happening, and to minimize the impact of Incidents that cannot be prevented. To this purpose he maintains information about Known Errors and Workarounds.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: The Problem Record contains all details of a Problem, documenting the history of the Problem from detection to resolution.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description
Prop.Value: The Known Error Database (KEDB) is created by Problem Management and used by Incident and Problem Management to manage all Known Error Records.
Prop.Label: Description

Prop.Name: sys_Description

Shape.Name: Annotation.189
Shape.Text: major Changes must be implemented via the Change and Release Management processes; standard (minor) Changes may be implemented without the involvement of Change Management

Shape.Text: If possible, find a temporary way of overcoming the Problem and document the Workaround in the Problem Record

Shape.Text: If possible, find a temporary way of overcoming the Problem and document the Workaround in the Problem Record

Shape.Name: Annotation.170
Shape.Text: research ways to solve the root cause of the Problem, using the CMS to identify and diagnose the exact point of failure

Shape.Text: in the case of standard (minor) Changes, Problem Management is authorized to immediately update the CMS

Shape.Name: Annotation.203
Shape.Text: apply tests or check with the user to ensure that the Problem is actually resolved

Shape.Text: so that if further Incidents arise the service can be restored more quickly
